
@startuml
' Define classes and their attributes

class School {
  -name: String
}

class Teacher {
  -firstName: String
  -lastName: String
  -email: String
}

class Student {
  -firstName: String
  -lastName: String
}

class Principal {
  -firstName: String
  -lastName: String
  -email: String
}

class Room {
  -name: String
}

class Classroom extends Room {
  -capacity: Integer
}

class Gym extends Room {
  -size: Integer
}

class ClassGroup {
  -name: String
}

' Define relationships

School "1" -- "1" Principal : has principal
School "1" -- "0..*" Teacher : employs
School "1" -- "0..*" Student : has students
Teacher "0..3" -- "1" School : teaches at
Student "1" -- "1" School : attends
Student "1" -- "1" ClassGroup : belongs to
ClassGroup "1" -- "1" Classroom : assigned to
ClassGroup "1" -- "0..*" Student : contains
Classroom "1" -- "1" Room : is a
Gym "1" -- "1" Room : is a
@enduml

### Explanation of Relationships:
- **School** has **exactly one Principal**, who is a **Teacher**.
- A **Teacher** can be employed by **one school** (though they may teach at up to three schools).
- A **Student** is enrolled in **exactly one School** and **exactly one ClassGroup**.
- A **ClassGroup** has between **10 and 31 Students** and is assigned to **exactly one Classroom**.
- **Classroom** and **Gym** are both types of **Room**.

